.TH simple_shell 1 "November 2025" "Version 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.RI [command ...]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B simple_shell
program is a basic command-line interpreter that reads input from the user, parses it into tokens, and executes commands.

It supports:
.IP \(bu 2
Running commands using \fBexecvp\fR
.IP \(bu 2
Forking child processes
.IP \(bu 2
Waiting for commands to finish
.IP \(bu 2
Built-in \fBexit\fR command

.SH USAGE
After starting the shell:

.EX
$ ./hsh
$ ls -l
$ echo hello
$ exit
.EE

.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success.

.SH AUTHORS
See AUTHORS file.
